---
import TerminalPreview from '../components/TerminalPreview.astro'
import SiteLayout from '../layouts/SiteLayout.astro'
// cspell:ignore tlsv
const canonical = 'https://terminal.santi020k.com/zsh/'
const description = 'Install a curated, fast Zsh setup with completions, suggestions, fuzzy search, smarter navigation, modern CLI tools, and the Santi020k Starship prompt.'
const brewInstall = 'brew install santi020k/tap/santi020k-terminal && santi020k-terminal install'
const scriptInstall = 'curl --proto \'=https\' --tlsv1.2 -fsSL https://terminal.santi020k.com/zsh/install.zsh | zsh'
const restart = 'exec zsh'
const schema = { '@context': 'https://schema.org', '@type': 'SoftwareApplication', name: 'Santi020k Zsh setup', applicationCategory: 'DeveloperApplication', operatingSystem: 'macOS', offers: { '@type': 'Offer', price: '0', priceCurrency: 'USD' }, url: canonical, downloadUrl: 'https://terminal.santi020k.com/zsh/install.zsh', description }
---
<SiteLayout title="Powerful Zsh Setup — Santi020k Terminal" {description} {canonical} {schema} image="og-zsh.png" imageAlt="Santi020k Zsh setup with completions, modern CLI tools, and Starship">
  <section class="shell hero"><div class="hero-copy"><p class="eyebrow">Curated Zsh setup</p><h1>A stronger shell in one command.</h1><p class="lede">A focused set of plugins and CLI tools for faster completion, command discovery, navigation, search, and Git—configured to work together without a heavy framework.</p><div class="actions"><a class="button primary" href="#install">Install the setup</a><a class="button secondary" href="/zsh/install.zsh">Read the installer</a></div><p class="compatibility"><span></span> macOS · Zsh · Homebrew · safe to run again</p></div><TerminalPreview prompt id="preview" /></section>
  <section class="shell section compact-section"><div class="section-heading"><p class="eyebrow">Small plugin layer</p><h2>Only the shell behavior that earns its place.</h2><p>Homebrew owns every dependency, so upgrades and removal stay familiar. No plugin manager or shell framework is required.</p></div><div class="feature-grid"><div><b>Autosuggestions</b><p>Reuse commands from history with a subtle inline suggestion.</p></div><div><b>Syntax highlighting</b><p>See valid commands and mistakes before pressing Return.</p></div><div><b>Extra completions</b><p>Add maintained completions for common developer commands.</p></div><div><b>Durable history</b><p>Share useful local history across sessions with duplicate control.</p></div></div></section>
  <section class="install-section" id="install"><div class="shell"><div class="section-heading"><p class="eyebrow">Two installation paths</p><h2>Choose how the setup is managed.</h2><p>Both options place configuration in <code>~/.config/santi020k-terminal</code>, back up files they manage, and add one source line to <code>~/.zshrc</code>. They do not replace your existing Zsh config.</p></div><div class="install-tabs" data-tabs><div class="tab-list" role="tablist" aria-label="Zsh installation method"><button id="zsh-brew-tab" role="tab" aria-selected="true" aria-controls="zsh-brew-panel">Homebrew · Recommended</button><button id="zsh-script-tab" role="tab" aria-selected="false" aria-controls="zsh-script-panel" tabindex="-1">Install script</button></div><div class="tab-panel" id="zsh-brew-panel" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="zsh-brew-tab"><h3>Install and manage the complete setup with Homebrew</h3><p>The formula owns the Santi020k CLI, theme assets, and dependencies. Configuration changes begin only when the explicit <code>install</code> command runs.</p><div class="command"><code>{brewInstall}</code><button data-copy={brewInstall} aria-label="Copy Homebrew installation command">Copy</button></div><aside class="notice"><b>Updates stay familiar</b><p>Run <code>brew upgrade</code> or <code>santi020k-terminal update</code> to update the package. The CLI also provides <code>doctor</code> and <code>uninstall</code>.</p></aside></div><div class="tab-panel" id="zsh-script-panel" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="zsh-script-tab" hidden><h3>Inspect and run the hosted installer</h3><p>The script uses Homebrew for the same dependencies, then downloads the current configuration directly from this site.</p><div class="command"><code>{scriptInstall}</code><button data-copy={scriptInstall} aria-label="Copy Zsh setup installer command">Copy</button></div><div class="actions"><a class="button secondary" href="/zsh/install.zsh">Read the installer</a></div></div></div><div class="simple-command-grid"><div><span>Start the new shell after either path</span><div class="command"><code>{restart}</code><button data-copy={restart} aria-label="Copy Zsh restart command">Copy</button></div></div></div></div></section>
  <section class="shell section"><div class="section-heading"><p class="eyebrow">Modern tool belt</p><h2>Faster defaults without hiding Unix.</h2><p>The setup installs proven tools and initializes only the ones that need shell integration. Every command remains available directly and can be removed with Homebrew.</p></div><div class="tool-list"><div><code>fzf</code><span>Fuzzy file, directory, and history search</span></div><div><code>zoxide</code><span>Directory jumping that learns where you work</span></div><div><code>eza</code><span>Modern, Git-aware directory listings</span></div><div><code>bat</code><span>Readable file output with syntax highlighting</span></div><div><code>rg + fd</code><span>Fast text and filesystem search</span></div><div><code>delta</code><span>Clearer Git diffs and code review output</span></div><div><code>jq</code><span>Reliable JSON querying and transformation</span></div><div><code>Starship</code><span>The matching Santi020k prompt</span></div></div></section>
</SiteLayout>
